<TITLE> Mahmud made BERC member in admin changes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 10 (bdnews24.com)Selim Mahmud, associate professor of department of law at the University of Dhaka, has been appointed a member of Bangladesh Energy Regulatory Commission, an establishment ministry order said Sunday. In another order, Bangladesh Parjatan Corporation chairman Shafique Alam Mehdi was appointed to Roads and Highways Department as additional secretary. Additional secretary Mizanur Rahman, an officer on special duty (OSD) at the establishment ministry, was appointed as chairman of the state tourism agency. Enamul Haque, OSD, was made member of National Curriculum and Textbook Board on deputation
